<script lang="ts">
  const html: string = "<h1>Headline</h1>\n\n<p>A headline is a page headline with heading, subtitle, and byline area. It provides a structured container for article or editorial page titles with supporting subtitle (dek) and author attribution.</p>\n\n<p>This headless component uses a <code>&lt;div&gt;</code> element containing a semantic heading element (<code>&lt;h1&gt;</code>-<code>&lt;h6&gt;</code>) at the specified level, with optional subtitle and byline slots.</p>\n\n<h2>Implementation Notes</h2>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Uses <code>&lt;div&gt;</code> container with a heading element at the specified level</li>\n<li>Default heading level is 1 (<code>&lt;h1&gt;</code>)</li>\n<li>Subtitle (dek) appears below the heading</li>\n<li>Byline slot for author/date attribution below the subtitle</li>\n<li>Inspired by Reuters Graphics Headline component</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>Props</h2>\n\n<ul>\n<li><code>level</code>: 1 | 2 | 3 | 4 | 5 | 6 (default: 1) -- heading level</li>\n<li><code>children</code>: slot (required) -- heading text content</li>\n<li><code>subtitle</code>: slot (optional) -- subtitle/dek content below heading</li>\n<li><code>byline</code>: slot (optional) -- byline area below subtitle</li>\n<li><code>...restProps</code>: Any additional HTML attributes</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>Usage</h2>\n\n<pre><code class=\"language-html\">&lt;Headline&gt;\n  Breaking: Major Policy Announcement\n  &lt;span slot=\"subtitle\"&gt;Government reveals new plan&lt;/span&gt;\n  &lt;Byline slot=\"byline\"&gt;By Jane Smith&lt;/Byline&gt;\n&lt;/Headline&gt;</code></pre>\n\n<pre><code class=\"language-html\">&lt;Headline level=\"2\"&gt;\n  Economic Analysis\n  &lt;span slot=\"subtitle\"&gt;Q1 results show steady growth across sectors&lt;/span&gt;\n&lt;/Headline&gt;</code></pre>\n\n<pre><code class=\"language-html\">&lt;Headline&gt;\n  The Future of Renewable Energy\n  &lt;span slot=\"subtitle\"&gt;How wind and solar are transforming the grid&lt;/span&gt;\n  &lt;Byline slot=\"byline\"&gt;\n    &lt;a href=\"/author/jane-smith\" rel=\"author\"&gt;Jane Smith&lt;/a&gt;\n  &lt;/Byline&gt;\n&lt;/Headline&gt;</code></pre>\n\n<h2>Keyboard Interactions</h2>\n\n<ul>\n<li>None</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>ARIA</h2>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Heading role from semantic heading element (<code>&lt;h1&gt;</code>-<code>&lt;h6&gt;</code>)</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>When to Use</h2>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Use for article or editorial page headlines with subtitle and attribution</li>\n<li>Use when you need a structured headline with a dek/subtitle below the main heading</li>\n<li>Use in combination with Byline component for author attribution</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>When Not to Use</h2>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Do not use for section headings within body text -- use plain heading elements</li>\n<li>Do not use for navigation headings -- use the appropriate navigation component</li>\n<li>Do not use when only a simple heading is needed without subtitle or byline</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>Headless</h2>\n\n<p>This component provides a <code>&lt;div&gt;</code> container with a semantic heading element, with zero visual styling. The consumer is responsible for all CSS including font sizes, spacing between heading, subtitle, and byline, text alignment, and responsive typography.</p>\n\n<h2>Styles</h2>\n\n<p>The consumer provides all CSS styling. The component renders with a <code>.headline</code> class for targeting. No default styles are included -- this is a fully headless component.</p>\n\n<h2>Testing</h2>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Verify the component renders a <code>&lt;div&gt;</code> element with class <code>headline</code></li>\n<li>Verify the heading element matches the specified level (default <code>&lt;h1&gt;</code>)</li>\n<li>Verify subtitle slot renders below the heading when provided</li>\n<li>Verify byline slot renders below the subtitle when provided</li>\n<li>Verify pass-through attributes are applied</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>Advice</h2>\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Designers</strong>: Keep headlines concise and scannable. Ensure subtitle text complements rather than repeats the headline. Consider responsive typography for different viewport sizes.</li>\n<li><strong>Developers</strong>: Always use the appropriate heading level for the page hierarchy. Do not skip heading levels. Use the Byline component within the byline slot for consistent author attribution.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>Related components</h2>\n\n<ul>\n<li><code>hero</code> — a large box or image with a title and description</li>\n<li><code>section-heading</code> — a styled heading introducing a major content section, with optional eyebrow and subtitle</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>References</h2>\n\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element\">MDN HTML elements reference</a></li>\n</ul>";
</script>

